eft class=m><span class=title>   Sign on for PoA</span><hr size=1> Looking to fill up 5 groups for PoA run.  The first 30 to sign up will be guarenteed a spot.  Any others that sign up will be the first considered as alternates and those that show up prior to raid may or may not make it in a group.<br>
<br>
Seeing how this is my very first raid on PoA, will someone notify me of where everyone usually meets?<br>
<br>
Main goal is to get atleast 2 lucky people a part of their epic.  Here is how i will handle the looting of these item(s) only.<br>
<br>
If you have atleast 20% of Epic quest complete you will get a bonus of +25 to your roll.<br>
If you have atleast 40% of Epic quest complete you will get a bonus of +50 to your roll.<br>
If you have atleast 60% of Epic quest complete you will get a bonus of +75 to your roll.<br>
If you have 80-99% of Epic complete and need the PoA drop, you will get a bonus of +100 to your roll.<br>
<br>
All bonus's above will only be awarded IF someone in your guild (if guilded) can verify the amount of the Epic quest you have left.<br>
<br>
Standard loot rule applies, +50 added for each level 51-60.<br>
<br>
GEMS and CASH Item drops:  <br>
Clerics I will give 1 or 2 gems of choice (depending on availability).  Limit of 1 specific type.  IE:  1 Blue Diamond.  Clerics may opt for a couple cash items as well.<br>
<br>
1 Gem will be given to the puller.  He or she will get to choose and the puller may opt for 2 cash items as well.<br>
<br>
All other Gems will be randomed.  Only 1 roll will be made.  Top 5 will select a Gem, then the next 5.  This will continue until all gems have been given out.<br>
<br>
Raid Leader will get to select 2 or 3 cash items.  All other items will be given out to those who didnt win any items.  Limit of up to 2 pieces.  Depending on available items left.<br>
<br>
I myself am hoping to complete 1 of the warrior tests.  If possible, if not there will be other times.<br>
<br>
Had alot of fun on the Hate raid and hope this one turns out to be just as fun.<br>
<br>
DATE and TIME of raid.  January 19th at 4:30pm PST.  This may be pushed back to no later than 5:30pm PST depending on if the later time will be more convenient for as many to show as possible. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/ujkorik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jkorik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(1/12/02 6:53:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/feqtestregistryfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sign on for PoA</span><hr size=1> PS:  Level bonus and Epic Quest completion bonus DO STACK! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#292929><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/beqtestregistry.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=pikelbouldershoulder>Pikel Bouldershoulder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(1/12/02 6:57:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/feqtestregistryfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sign on for PoA</span><hr size=1> I've never been to Air.  Time I go take a look.  Sign me up.<br>
